     Look for possible enhancement of Dayton Hudson's charitable

     Look for possible enhancement of Dayton Hudson's charitable
giving policies since the corporation's $1.04 billion acquisition
of Marshall Field's, announced in April.  Marshall Field's 24
stores, located in Illinois, Wisconsin, Texas, and Ohio, will
bring Dayton Hudson's total number of department stores to 61.
It is too soon to speculate on changes in corporate giving, a
Dayton Hudson spokesman said, "but if the merger is successful,
Marshall Field's will become a part of our culture, and the
foundation is a big part of that culture."  The Dayton Hudson
Foundation gave $17.4 million in 1988, chiefly to the arts and
humanities and social services.  Cynthia Mayeda was recently
named director of the foundation (CGW, April).



