INDUSTRIES AND WORLD MARKETS:  A SAMPLING OF THE U.S. EXPERIENCE IN
THE 1980S

By Economics Division and Science Policy Research Division.
Coordinated by Bernard Gelb.  72 pages.  While some U.S. industries
are having considerable difficulty competing against their foreign
counterparts, some are holding their own, and some are doing quite
well.  This report analyzes the experience of a number of U.S.
industries during the past decade or so, and makes some observations
about the diversity of their fortunes in the context of their
individual natures and structures.  Order No. 92-302 E.

The full report, as described above and authored by the Congressional
Research Service, costs $47 from Penny Hill Press, 6440 Wiscasset
Road, Bethesda, MD  20816, 301-229-8229.



