AIDS:  INTERNATIONAL PERSPECTIVES AND ISSUES:  BIBLIOGRAPHY-IN-BRIEF

By Bonnie F. Managan, Library Services Division.  The acquired immune
deficiency syndrome (AIDS) is a worldwide health problem that will
have significant impact on developing countries.  By the end of the
century, the World Health Organization estimates that 90 percent of
the projected 25 million to 30 million cases of human
immunodeficiency virus (HIV) infection will be in developing
countries.  This bibliography focuses on AIDS in Africa, America
(outside of the United States), Asia, and Europe.  Order No. 92-283
L.

