FEDERAL FUNDING FOR AIDS RESEARCH AND PREVENTION:  FY81-FY93

By Judith A. Johnson, Science Policy Research Division.  23 pages.
This report provides a synopsis of the budget activity relating to
AIDS from the discovery of the disease in 1981 through FY 1993.
Federal funding for AIDS research and prevention has increased from
$200,000 in FY 1981 to $1,967,257,000 in FY 1992.  Governmentwide
spending on AIDS is estimated at over $4,360,000,000 in FY 1992.
Order No. 92-328 SPR.

