THE PRESIDENT'S HEALTH CARE REFORM PROPOSAL

By Education and Public Welfare Division.  82 pages.  On February 6,
1992, President Bush issued his Comprehensive Health Care Reform
program, a plan designed to make health care more accessible by
making health insurance more affordable and the health care system
more efficient.  The program uses market forces to implement reforms
