SOCIAL SECURITY:  THE EFFECT OF ECONOMIC VARIATIONS ON BENEFITS

By Geoffrey C. Kollmann, Education and Public Welfare Division.  19
pages.  Social security is designed to produce uniform benefit levels
over time.  However, in fact these benefits vary depending on the
economic conditions prevailing when a worker becomes eligible for
benefits.  This report shows the instability in benefit levels that
would occur under the economic conditions that occurred in 1966-1990.
