TAX RATES AND THE MARRIAGE PENALTY

By Robert B. Burdette, American Law Division.  2 pages.  This report
examines the rate schedules and tables applied for purposes of
calculating liability under the federal income tax.  One frequently
asked question concerning the rate schedules is why taxable income
reported by an unmarried individual is taxed at a higher rate than a
like amount of taxable income reported by a married couple filing
jointly.  This is an anomaly of having graduated rates applicable to
different types of taxpayers.  Order No. 92-319 A.

