NATIONAL LABOR RELATIONS BOARD:  ACTION NEEDED TO IMPROVE
CASE-PROCESSING TIME AT HEADQUARTERS

Order No.:  GAO/HRD-91-29
Pages:  72

The National Labor Relations Board generally considers cases
involving either allegations of unfair labor practices or
disagreements about elections on union representation. In
response to concerns about the length of time it has taken
to decide some cases appealed to the headquarters Board from
the regional offices, GAO looked at the Board's system for
deciding cases. This report (1) describes how long the Board
had taken to decide cases, particularly since 1984, and
determines whether  there were any excessive delays; (2)
identifies factors that contributed to such delays; and (3)
determines if additional administrative or legislative
