FTC:WATCH via NewsNet
January 17, 1996

Persist in prior approval?


Hoechst A.G.  and its U.S.  subsidiaries have asked the FTC whether they
should continue to ask the FTC for approval every time they want to buy acetal
assets.  A 1991 consent order requires the firms to seek prior approval before
such acquisitions.  The Commission policy on prior approval provisions in
orders has changed since 1991.

REFERENCE: FTC Press Advisory, January 2; 
D-9216; Contact: Daniel P. Ducore, 202/326-2526


S.C.  Johnson & Son, Inc.  asked much the same a few months ago, and the
agency has now set aside a 1993 order against the company.  The prior approval
provision was the only obligation left in the order.

REFERENCE: FTC Press Advisory, December 28; 
C-3418; Contact: Daniel P. Ducore, 202/326-2526







