BROOKINGS FOCUSES ON HEALTH CARE

The Brookings Institution has issued two major studies focusing on 
aspects of health care.
 
PERSONS WITH DISABILITIES:  ISSUES IN HEALTH CARE FINANCING AND 
SERVICE DELIVERY, 324 pages, $16.95, analyzes the acute and long-term 
needs of disabled Americans.  Included are sections on the market for 
private insurance and expenditures for health care.
 
THE PROBLEM THAT WON'T GO AWAY:  REFORMING U.S. HEALTH CARE 
FINANCING, 298 pages, $16.95, suggests that comprehensive reform is 
not the way to go.  Rather, "bit-size" changes in health care 
financing are likely to be more widely accepted.
 
Both are available from The Brookings Book Store, 1775 Massachusetts 
Avenue, N.W., Washington, DC  20036, 800-275-1447 or 202-797-6258; 
fax 202-797-6004.



