"It combines casualness of speech with the permanence of
writing.  It's got a lot of potential for embarrassing the
other side," says Hartford, Conn., lawyer Allan B. Taylor,
explaining why lawyers like to pour over electronic mail for
evidence, quoted by CONNECTICUT LAW TRIBUNE, Dec. 18, 1995.




